<text>
    <group>
       
    
    <!-- type is letter -->

    
        
        <pb n="6555" facs="#L1916_2415_img_6555"/>
            <text type="letter" decls="#corresp1">
                <body>
                    

<opener><dateline><date>19. Dec 15</date></dateline>
<salute><hi rend="underline">My</hi> Pr.</salute></opener>
<p>If a little pr imagined for a minute that a bw would be content
<lb/>to put away a letter for 6 days she is an even more curious creature
<lb/>that even he thought. However he is very good, &amp; this  letter will be 
<lb/>reread on the 24 <hi rend="superscript">th</hi> !</p>
<p> Whilst I believe I can quite well defer m Xmas greetings 
<lb/>till Tuesday, you will take notice that the BW will endeavour hard
<lb/>not to forget about a pr on the 25<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>, unless of course he is very busy! </p>
<p>I shall not be able to write tomorrow as I am going up to 
<lb/>see the 107 Bge I hope. At any rate I have made the suggestion
<lb/>to the 9 RIR, &amp; trust they make take the proposal - not as a beastly
<lb/><unclear>ban</unclear> - but as a sign that they are not entirely forgotten by the remainder
<lb/>of the Ulster Div.</p>
<p>I am alone in the office as <add>the 2</add> Ro have gone out on a boar
<lb/>shoot with the General. I was not very keen as it is sunday &amp;
<lb/> I proposed  my visit to the 107<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>as my return.  </p>
<p>Yesterday Richardson &amp; I went with the General on a 
<lb/>tour. Russell took the view that the Gen' would not want us
<lb/>but I rather took the line that we ought to be with him
<lb/>when he was doing this particular work, &amp; as a matter of fact
<lb/>he seemed quite <add>well</add> pleased that we should. There is something 
<lb/> up between the Gen' &amp; Russell which I cannot understand, unless it 
<lb/>is that the latter's politeness is getting on the former's nerves.
<lb/> Russell is certainly rather dumped at present &amp; it  is possible that the Gen'
        
    

    
         
        <pb n="6556" facs="#L1916_2415_img_6556"/>
        
        
           
            has told him that he does not<lb/>
recommend him for higher appointment<lb/>
which is probably the<lb/>
case with us all.  Mayne has decided to relinquish his job in order<lb/>
to become ADC again to Sir A Murray who is going our to the Mediterranean<lb/>
probably as C in C   I am sorry he is going.</p>

<p>Tell Sue that I did not know she was a 'little bear'  I thought all<lb/>
my sisters were flowers, I certainly married one of the family as such, &amp; found<lb/>
&#x2014; to my horror of course! &#x2014; that she changed into an animal.  Are the others<lb/>
also going to do this? My leave will be even more uncertain till you reply <add>&amp; reassure me</add></p>

<p>Don't write more than a <unclear>p c</unclear> when you have a headache old<lb/>
thing.  I shan't grumble.</p>

<p>They are very busy <unclear>hunting</unclear> at the front, supposed to be for us, but all<lb/>
plans may change now.  I will not write about the changes as you know<lb/>
my views about Douglas Haig.  I hear Butler is to be chief of Staff!  He is a<lb/>
good fellow but we never expected this.  If I wrote to him I could probably get a<lb/>
lift but think I prefer to remain an obscure wild animal with a clean paw<lb/>
in this respect.  Only 6 years ago he was acting as my Chief of Staff on a staff ride!<lb/></p>

<p>I have written a stupid letter to mother but she will<lb/>
understand that I write under difficulties.  I will answer the 3<lb/>
other letters for the New Year, unless I turn up?</p>

<p>The General was to have started on his boar hunt in the dark<lb/>
I took the opportunity of a laze bed till nearly 8, &amp; only just missed<lb/>
him when I came down!</p>

<p>I hope to send you later Xmas wishes, &amp; you will<lb/>
also have time to send me another batch perhaps?  Any how I<lb/>
shan't forget the little animal which keeps disturbing me
</p>
<closer><salute>Your b w</salute>
<signed>Wilfrid B Spender</signed></closer>

<note><date>19 Dec</date></note>
        
    
                </body>
            </text>

        
            
        
            
        

         

